{"TopicId":140765,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Suggestion: Kerbal Galaxy","CreatedByName":"The_Rocketeer","CreatedById":81727,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T19:00:59Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"The_Rocketeer","CreatedById":81727,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T19:00:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSuper-simple idea but possibly very complicated to implement / too demanding on system resources, but whatever.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nRecipe for Kerbal Galaxy (serves any number).\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nReplace the Sun with a galactic core/black hole type body.\u003Cbr\u003E\nReplace the planets with stars.\u003Cbr\u003E\nReplace moons with planets.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAdd moons to new planets.\u003Cbr\u003E\nScale up to galactic (KSP-scale) proportions.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nSpiral arms wouldn\u0027t work well in KSP, but who cares? You still have multiple star systems to visit in an inter-stellar system that makes Kerbal sense.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"spacebrick3","CreatedById":158990,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T20:16:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure this is viable in the near future, because Squad will probably want to work on making the game better, but \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113260\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sigma88\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0has made a mod that does this for most planet packs:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/116058-wip112-galactic-neighborhood/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T21:12:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe \u0022add new planets/stars\u0022 is on the \u0022no ask\u0022 list\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The_Rocketeer","CreatedById":81727,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-29T21:24:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113260\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sigma88\u003C/a\u003E (big fan btw):\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nWhere is the \u0027no ask\u0027 list? I looked but did not find.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nReally, though, I\u0027m not actually asking for anything. I\u0027m suggesting a way to expand KSP one astronomical step up from system of planets to system of stars. I don\u0027t really mind if every solar system is identical to the current one, since for me the challenge of getting somewhere is always more interesting than the doing of things when I get there. If your Galactic Neighborhood mod is basically what I\u0027m talking about, I must\u0027ve missed it so that\u0027s one more for me to try out \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-29T21:25:19Z\u0022 title=\u002205/29/2016 09:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by The_Rocketeer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T13:57:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u0022What Not To Suggest\u0022 list is deprecated. You can check the \u0022Links to Common Suggestions\u0022 sticky in this forum for largish threads about popular topics (don\u0027t recall offhand if this one is covered).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hay","CreatedById":132918,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-31T07:40:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe something like the Firefly galaxy?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-31T11:02:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222609321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140765\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464680459\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Hay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe something like the Firefly galaxy?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirefly had a single solar system. I\u0027m somewhat surprised there isn\u0027t a mod for it already (or is there?).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The_Rocketeer","CreatedById":81727,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-31T13:32:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222609321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140765\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464680459\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Hay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe something like the Firefly galaxy?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222609525\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140765\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464692526\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirefly had a single solar system. I\u0027m somewhat surprised there isn\u0027t a mod for it already (or is there?).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRIC is right (tho it was a multiple star system), but this is still a wonderful idea!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"stibbons","CreatedById":57865,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-31T14:17:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222609525\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140765\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464692526\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirefly had a single solar system. I\u0027m somewhat surprised there isn\u0027t a mod for it already (or is there?).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s been discussion about it recently, and I think \u0022\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003EThe Firefly Verse consists of one central star, which is orbited by 4 other stars, 7 artificial or proto-stars, and about 260 planets and moons\u0022 explains why it hasn\u0027t been done.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/135206-firefly-solar-system/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Holo","CreatedById":39606,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-10T06:00:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore places to visit = more good. I\u0027m for this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}